20gay%20cocktail%20bar%2C%20ICONS.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20but%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20at%20the%20age%20of%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJohn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20was%20raised%20Mormon%20and%20homeschooled%20in%20West%20Virginia.%20I%20attended%20Brigham%20Young%20University%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20until%20I%20discovered%20some%20things%20about%20myself%20that%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbisexual-grew-up-mormon-convinced-myself-straight-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealign%20with%20the%20Mormon%20Church%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20met%20doing%20a%20show%20in%20Connecticut.%20The%20rest%20is%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJohn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEven%20while%20living%20in%20New%20York%2C%20we%20visited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-springs-becoming-smart-city-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColorado%20Springs%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20lot.%20We%20went%20back%20and%20forth%20and%20taught%20master%20classes%20and%20workshops%20for%20kids%20at%20an%20art%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20school%20asked%20if%20I%20had%20time%20to%20lead%20their%20theatre%20program%20for%20a%20semester.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%2C%20long-term%20idea.%20That%20inspired%20us%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20could%20feel%20the%20energy%20growing%20in%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20so%20we%20figured%20it%20was%20a%20smart%20move.%20It%20was%20still%20affordable%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20bought%20the%20Colorado%20Springs%20house%20in%202018.%20We%20were%20still%20doing%20shows%20in%20New%20York%2C%20so%20we%20made%20it%20into%20an%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-new-york-amid-coronavirus-pandemic-wondering-about-return-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epandemic%20happened%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20Colorado%20instead%20of%20staying%20in%20our%20400-square-foot%20studio%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20never%20the%20plan%20to%20fully%20move%20to%20Colorado%2C%20but%20fate%20had%20different%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226aa6d685-5645-4882-b8bc-75f5e155a53d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20thought%20Colorado%20would%20be%20temporary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20wasn't%20one%20moment%20we%20decided%20to%20move%20out%20of%20New%20York.%20It%20was%20a%20slow%20progression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJohn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Neither%20Josh%20nor%20I%20are%20very%20good%20at%20sitting%20idle.%20But%20COVID%20forced%20us%20to%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20meeting%20people%20at%20socially-distanced%20neighborhood%20gatherings.%20We%20realized%20what%20a%20vibrant%20and%20diverse%20community%20Colorado%20Springs%20had%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22John%20Wolfe%20and%20Josh%20Franklin%20photographed%20from%20behind%20in%20front%20of%20Colorado%20mountains%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a99a5afb6d32635ee5267a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn%20Wolfe%20and%20Josh%20Franklin%20said%20they%20love%20the%20small-town%20charm%20of%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20easy%20access%20to%20the%20mountains.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20John%20Wolfe%20and%20Josh%20Franklin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20the%20city%20needed%20a%20dedicated%20queer%20space%20downtown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20silly%20little%20COVID%20idea%20that%20snowballed.%20People%20got%20really%20excited%2C%20and%20it%20took%20off%20without%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20a%20great%20deal%20on%20a%20rental%20space%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20We%20did%20all%20the%20work%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20thought%20ICONS%20would%20be%20a%20sleepy%2C%20little%20cocktail%20piano%20bar.%20But%20it%20exploded%20when%20we%20officially%20opened%20on%20Halloween%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20was%20a%20party.%20And%20it's%20been%20a%20party%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20able%20to%20staff%20ICONS%20with%20professional%20singers.%20It's%20very%20New%20York.%20We%20wanted%20to%20bring%20what%20we%20were%20passionate%20about%20to%20Colorado%20Springs%20and%20share%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20first%20year%2C%20we%20were%20voted%20best%20new%20bar%20and%20best%20overall%20bar.%20We%20couldn't%20believe%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220fd0cb99-d425-46ef-bcde-0ce11c087b3e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20were%20expecting%20pushback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJosh%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPeople%20warned%20us.%20They%20said%20we%20shouldn't%20call%20it%20a%20gay%20bar.%20They%20liked%20our%20concept%20but%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20just%20the%20opposite.%20We%20didn't%20get%20one%20piece%20of%20hate%20or%20pushback.%20To%20see%20it%20be%20so%20celebrated%20was%20rewarding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20told%20teenage%20me%20that%20a%20gay%20bar%20would%20be%20voted%20best%20bar%20in%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20I%20would%20have%20said%20you%20were%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColorado%20Springs%20was%20extremely%20conservative%20when%20I%20was%20growing%20up.%20There%20was%20an%20amendment%20passed%20in%20the%20nineties%20that%20essentially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F06%2F05%2Fus%2Fcolorado-masterpiece-cake.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallowed%20businesses%20in%20the%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20discriminate%20against%20gay%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20to%20get%20to%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I've%20found%20such%20beauty%20in%20this%20full-circle%20moment%2C%20coming%20back%20to%20Colorado%20after%20the%20experiences%20I%20had%20here%20in%20high%20school%20and%20being%20able%20to%20offer%20the%20community%20a%20bright%2C%20celebratory%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJohn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20number%20of%20changes%20we've%20seen%20happen%20for%20people%20because%20of%20our%20space%20has%20been%20amazing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinally-came-out-gay-in-my-fifties-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople%20have%20come%20out%20to%20their%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20to%20themselves%20because%20of%20ICONs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20photos%20of%20John%20and%20Josh%20walking%20their%20dogs%20and%20a%20crowd%20of%20people%20enjoying%20live%20music%20in%20ICONS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a999bc1a227600e632fa69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn%20and%20Josh%20opened%20ICONS%20(right)%20in%20Colorado%20Springs%20in%202020.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20John%20Wolfe%20and%20Josh%20Franklin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d105af19-8a79-4a6d-939d-1e310e07c62d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EColorado%20Springs%20has%20a%20small-town%20feel%20with%20big-city%20amenities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJohn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20downtown%20area%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20little%20cities%20in%20the%20world.%20And%20it's%20changing%20quickly.%20There's%20a%20huge%20influx%20of%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20chains%20downtown.%20It's%20mostly%20small%20businesses.%20All%20the%20owners%20know%20each%20other%20and%20support%20one%20another